dcterms:creator: S. E. Z. Soudjani
R. Majumdar
T. Nagapetyan
dcterms:description: The temperature dataset models a controller keeping the temperature of a room within set bounds. The discontinuity arises from the discrete state of the controller, being either on or off. The model has a 41-dimensional latent variable and 80 if-statements.
dcterms:title: temperature

dcterms:creator: C. Mak
C. L. Ong
H. Paquet
D. Wagner
dcterms:description: The random-walk dataset models a random walk of bounded length. The goal is to infer the starting position based on the distance walked. The walk stops as soon as the destination is reached, which is checked using if-statements. The model has a 16-dimensional latent variable and 31 if-statements.
dcterms:title: random-walk

dcterms:creator: W. Lee
H. Yu
H. Yang
dcterms:description: The xornet dataset is a multi-layer neural network trained to compute the XOR function with all activation functions being the Heaviside step function. The model has a 25-dimensional latent space and 28 if-statements.
dcterms:title: xornet

dcterms:creator: B. Khajwal
C. L. Ong
D. Wagner
dcterms:description: The F2 dataset can be viewed as a simplification of xornet. It is the only model in which the guards of if-statements contain variables which depend on branching. The model corresponds to a term in Expr3.
dcterms:title: F2

dcterms:creator: C. Davidson-Pilon
dcterms:description: The cheating dataset simulates a differential privacy setting where students taking an exam are surveyed to determine the prevalence of cheating without exposing the details for any individual. The model has 300 if-statements and a 301-dimensional latent space.
dcterms:title: cheating

dcterms:creator: C. Davidson-Pilon
dcterms:description: The textmsg dataset models daily text message rates, aiming to discover a change in the rate over a 74-day period. The model has a 3-dimensional latent variable and 37 if-statements.
dcterms:title: textmsg

dcterms:creator: R. H. Shumway
D. S. Stoffer
dcterms:description: The influenza dataset models the US influenza mortality for 1969, where the mortality rate depends on the dominant virus strain. The model has a 37-dimensional latent variable and 24 if-statements.
dcterms:title: influenza
